akn:section.akn:heading: Moneys in the Rural Electrification and Telephone Revolving Fund

akn:content.akn:p:
§ 933. Moneys in the Rural Electrification and Telephone Revolving Fund Moneys in the fund shall remain on deposit in the Treasury of the United States until disbursed. (May 20, 1936, ch. 432, title III, § 303, as added Pub. L. 93–32, § 2, May 11, 1973, 87 Stat. 67.)
Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries Effective DateSection effective May 11, 1973, see section 12 of Pub. L. 93–32, set out as a note under section 930 of this title.
